      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOORAH PHILTRA (3) finished eighth at Melton two starts back then was highly competitive at his latest appearance over 1720m at the same circuit, beaten only 2 metres into second after being close to the pace throughout. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Finds a nice race and can go take this out. DHAULAGIRI NZ (10) scored last time out by 2.5 metres at Mildura over 2190m after an encouraging minor placing the start before. Not drawn to best so may need a 10/10 drive. Must raise the bar but another win is not out of the question. MERRYWOOD PAUL (2) disappointed last time when eighth over 2240m at Melton. Can atone. CRIME WRITER (8) only finished eighth over 1720m at Melton last start but racing in an easier line-up here can return to top-three form.",
